{\pard\qc\b\fs36\cf1 REDSHIFT ODBC COMMUNITY EDITION\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs28\cf1 Version 2.1.13.1 (Build Level 1)\par}
\par

{\b\fs28\cf2 IMPORTANT INFORMATION}\par
\par
This is a COMMUNITY-MAINTAINED version of the Amazon Redshift ODBC Driver.\par
This is NOT an official Amazon Web Services product and is NOT supported by AWS.\par
\par

{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 VERSION INFORMATION\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
\pard\par

{\b Community Edition:} v2.1.13.1 (Build Level 1)\par
{\b Based on:} AWS Amazon Redshift ODBC Driver v2.1.13\par
{\b Release Date:} February 24, 2026\par
{\b Maintained by:} Redshift ODBC Community\par
{\b Source Repository:} https://github.com/ORELASH/amazon-redshift-odbc-driver\par
\par

{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 COMMUNITY ENHANCEMENTS (Build Level 1)\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
\pard\par

This Community Edition includes the following enhancements beyond the official AWS v2.1.13 release:\par
\par

{\b\fs26\cf4 CRITICAL FIXES}\par
\par

{\b 1. UNSPECIFIEDOID (OID 0) Handling}\par
   \bullet  Fixed handling of unknown data types by mapping OID 0 to LONGVARCHAR\par
   \bullet  Resolves "Unknown SQL type" errors with certain Redshift functions\par
   \bullet  Improves compatibility with functions like pg_get_session_roles()\par
\par

{\b 2. Azure OAuth2 Cancel Detection}\par
   \bullet  Immediate error when user cancels Azure AD login\par
   \bullet  Clear error message when browser is closed during authentication\par
   \bullet  Validates authorization code before proceeding\par
   \bullet  No more waiting for timeout when authentication fails\par
\par

{\b 3. Browser Disconnection Early Detection}\par
   \bullet  Detects browser disconnection within seconds (not minutes)\par
   \bullet  Maximum 3 consecutive empty requests before exiting\par
   \bullet  Comprehensive logging for debugging OAuth issues\par
   \bullet  Significantly improves user experience\par
\par

{\b\fs26\cf4 BUILD SYSTEM IMPROVEMENTS}\par
\par

{\b 4. GitHub Actions CI/CD Automation}\par
   \bullet  Automated MSI building on Windows Server 2022\par
   \bullet  Reproducible builds without local Windows machine\par
   \bullet  SHA256 checksums for all builds\par
   \bullet  Build artifacts retained for 90 days\par
\par

{\b 5. vcpkg Dependency Management}\par
   \bullet  Consistent, reproducible builds\par
   \bullet  Version-locked dependencies\par
   \bullet  Automated installation of OpenSSL, AWS SDK, c-ares\par
\par

{\b 6. Azure OAuth2 v2.0 Endpoints}\par
   \bullet  Consistent use of Microsoft Identity v2.0 endpoints\par
   \bullet  Proper PKCE (RFC 7636) support\par
   \bullet  Support for client_secret (confidential clients)\par
   \bullet  Fixes authentication freeze issues\par
\par

{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 AWS OFFICIAL BASE (v2.1.13)\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
\pard\par

The Community Edition is based on AWS Amazon Redshift ODBC Driver v2.1.13, which includes:\par
\par

1. Improved error handling and SQL state reporting\par
2. SQLGetTypeInfo dynamic column names based on ODBC version\par
3. SQL_DESC_CONCISE_TYPE synchronization (ODBC spec compliance)\par
4. Corrected ARD, APD, IPD descriptor default values\par
5. Proper error messages for non-readable/writable descriptor fields\par
6. Length indicators for non-string data types\par
7. Enhanced escape clause handling with additional function support\par
8. Improved IAM JWT authentication logging\par
9. IdC Browser authentication proxy support\par
10. Region priority fixes for CNAME connections\par
11. SQLGetData numeric type octet length fix\par
12. macOS build compatibility improvements\par
\par

{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 USE CASES\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
\pard\par

{\b\cf4 This Community Edition is suitable for:}\par
\par
\cf4 \uc10003 \cf3 Development and testing environments\par
\cf4 \uc10003 \cf3 Azure AD OAuth2 authentication scenarios\par
\cf4 \uc10003 \cf3 Organizations requiring immediate error feedback on auth failures\par
\cf4 \uc10003 \cf3 Environments where UNSPECIFIEDOID types are encountered\par
\cf4 \uc10003 \cf3 CI/CD pipelines requiring reproducible builds\par
\par

{\b\cf2 NOT recommended for:}\par
\par
\cf2 \uc10007 \cf3 Production systems without thorough testing\par
\cf2 \uc10007 \cf3 Environments requiring official AWS support\par
\cf2 \uc10007 \cf3 Compliance scenarios requiring certified software\par
\par

