{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 INSTALLATION AND USAGE\par}
{\pard\qc\b\fs24\cf3 ============================================\par}
\pard\par

{\b\fs26\cf4 Basic Installation}\par
1. Download RedshiftODBC-Community-v2.1.13.1.msi\par
2. Verify SHA256 checksum\par
3. Run MSI installer (requires Administrator privileges)\par
4. Configure ODBC DSN using ODBC Data Source Administrator\par
\par

{\b\fs26\cf4 Azure OAuth2 Configuration}\par
Connection string example:\par
\par
{\f1\fs20
Driver=\{Amazon Redshift (x64)\};\par
Server=your-cluster.region.redshift.amazonaws.com;\par
Database=dev;\par
UID=;\par
PWD=;\par
Auth_Type=IAM;\par
Plugin_Name=BrowserAzureADOAuth2;\par
idp_tenant=your-tenant-id;\par
client_id=your-client-id;\par
idp_response_timeout=120;\par
}
\par

{\b\fs26\cf4 Common Issues}\par
\bullet  Authentication timeout: Increase idp_response_timeout\par
\bullet  Browser not opening: Check firewall and proxy settings\par
\bullet  OID errors: Fixed in this version with UNSPECIFIEDOID handling\par
\par

